{"author":"RebarBotNava","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Problem\nThe `rebar-brainstorm` skill (examples/agent-skills/rebar-brainstorm/SKILL.md) tells the\nauthor to run the plan-review gate on *each* ticket immediately after creating them, before\nany dependency links exist and regardless of blocked state. This contradicts the actual gate\nbehavior documented in AGENTS.md / docs/plan-review-gate.md: `rebar review-plan` fast-fails\nwith no LLM (unsigned INDETERMINATE, exit 2) on a ticket that is not yet claimable — one still\n`open` but blocked by an unclosed dependency — and reviews are dependency-scoped so they must\nrun in dependency order (prerequisites/children before dependents), never in parallel.\n\n## Approach\nRewrite the \"Before recording tickets, read the project's plan-review gate\" section of\nrebar-brainstorm/SKILL.md so that, after creating tickets, the author FIRST establishes the\ndependency graph between children (link via blocks/depends_on), then runs plan-review ONLY on\nunblocked tickets (identified by `rebar ready`), in dependency order, reviewing later tickets\nas their dependencies close and they become unblocked. Include a fallback: if `rebar ready`\nreturns an empty set, the graph likely has a cycle/authoring error — inspect and resolve before\nproceeding. Rationale: authoring to the real gate protocol avoids a guaranteed no-LLM\nfast-fail and matches AGENTS.md's dependency-order review rule; it is far cheaper than\ndiscovering the exit-2 at review time.\n\nAlso assess rebar-implement/SKILL.md: it is an executor of an already-decomposed epic and\nalready claims/reviews only the unblocked, dependency-ordered set via `rebar ready`/\n`next-batch`, treating the dependency graph as a precondition — so it needs no change. This\nassessment is part of the ticket's scope (documented outcome: no edit, rationale recorded).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] rebar-brainstorm/SKILL.md's plan-review section states plan-review is run only on\n  unblocked tickets, after the child dependency graph (blocks/depends_on links) is established,\n  in dependency order — verified by reading the edited section (grep shows \"unblocked\" and\n  \"dependency order\" in the section).\n- [ ] The section references the no-LLM fast-fail (exit 2 / INDETERMINATE) on still-blocked\n  tickets and names `rebar ready` for identifying the unblocked set — verified by reading the\n  section.\n- [ ] The section specifies a fallback for when `rebar ready` returns an empty set (diagnose\n  the dependency graph for a cycle/authoring error and resolve before proceeding) — verified by\n  reading the section.\n- [ ] rebar-implement/SKILL.md is left byte-for-byte unchanged (verified by\n  `git diff --stat origin/main -- examples/agent-skills/rebar-implement/SKILL.md` showing no\n  change), and the no-edit assessment rationale is recorded as a comment on this ticket.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] Change lands on main through Gerrit — proven by recording the Gerrit\n  change number and the LLM-Review +1 / Verified +1 vote outcomes as a comment on this ticket\n  before close."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784869345051295001,"uuid":"2921b3b6-e41b-4e06-bb4e-318d7fe7af6c"}